<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 16 at 2:19AM CST  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...Band of light snow has developed...
At 2:15 AM, a band of light snow has developed from Texline east
towards areas north of Dalhart, to Stratford, and north of
Spearman. Light snowfall accumulations up to an inch, with
locally higher amounts possible as the snow band moves south.
Reduced visibilities along with some snow covered roadways are
possible under the band of snow. Please use caution if traveling.</description>
